	<Text>The Army Meritorious Service Medal was introduced on 19 December 1845. The medal was introduced, with an annual annuity, to recognise meritorious service by Segeants and other senior NCOs. It could be awarded immediately if they had performed especially meritorious service in difficult circumstances.</Text>
